<subSubSection id="C24B9FA5C772C04A4FC4EE24C5C5A09D" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6EED9806B504E7B071B64F9B15A569BC" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7D17A99D763F253573BE0D177979EB8" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="093043C257C6BBFD94CCFE51FEFDC711" authorityName="Bordera &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites perinetensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perinetensis">
<emphasis id="E94AE78D65F6CD8A696FCDB7F3C2A858" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites perinetensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="2506BB8D1BEC704A4C70636E3AA64780" authorityName="Seyrig" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6802DD94614E4CA91722D950C011CD61" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the combination of the following characters: pronotum mostly smooth and shiny, longitudinally strigose punctate at the dorsal lateral part (Figs 
<figureCitation id="383FC7644BE46A41F3D66ABE71A33EBC" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Piasites perinetensis sp. nov., female (holotype): A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C head and mesoscutum, dorsal view D head and mesosoma, lateral view E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B); 0.2 mm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677626" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">8D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1821DB78761C6B3C43BC32D9A50D936B" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13E</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum evenly convex, mostly smooth and shiny (Figs 
<figureCitation id="9C9F1E6338A91ACDF11D1ABB563975C7" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Piasites perinetensis sp. nov., female (holotype): A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C head and mesoscutum, dorsal view D head and mesosoma, lateral view E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B); 0.2 mm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677626" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">8C, D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="AC8050A9D34D0CC03CA7896F5BFBC9BB" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13E</figureCitation>
); metapleuron finely transversally striate (Figs 
<figureCitation id="D22BE03E8B5CA51BDF3D6CF0BC24B5F2" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Piasites perinetensis sp. nov., female (holotype): A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C head and mesoscutum, dorsal view D head and mesosoma, lateral view E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B); 0.2 mm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677626" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">8D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="46F1D050E678CE42B716AED38BF3B9D3" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13G</figureCitation>
); propodeum strongly rugose, posterior transverse carina very weak without forming lateral crests, merging in the central part with the strong rugosities of the propodeum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="56771B602173172B78AC4391623813BA" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Propodeum of Piasites, dorsal view, females (I): A P. carinatus Seyrig B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. politus sp. nov. (paratype) D P. perinetensis sp. nov. (holotype). Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677618" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">1D</figureCitation>
); outer ocular orbit extensively black (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DBA45932AF0F474D8A016CB5E11884A9" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Piasites perinetensis sp. nov., female (holotype): A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C head and mesoscutum, dorsal view D head and mesosoma, lateral view E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B); 0.2 mm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677626" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">8D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="94DB596C80ADCF14AF1CE14CF78F2BEA" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13E</figureCitation>
); propleuron, pronotum, mesoscutum, coxae and T1-3 orange (Figs 
<figureCitation id="5160F2E45920BCFC76CAD33F9D174A5B" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Piasites perinetensis sp. nov., female (holotype): A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C head and mesoscutum, dorsal view D head and mesosoma, lateral view E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B); 0.2 mm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677626" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">8A, D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="86237EE5702B08AB66F0338BF40C3A5C" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13D, E</figureCitation>
). Additionally, female and male have areolet about 0.60
<normalizedToken id="C3DE69F08400E5DF0AA22992C10EC6AC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AC6156FD3B6816A3C0062A75F1BFCE9C" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Piasites perinetensis sp. nov., female (holotype): A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C head and mesoscutum, dorsal view D head and mesosoma, lateral view E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B); 0.2 mm (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677626" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">8E</figureCitation>
) and 0.45
<normalizedToken id="557DA9B420A584AE4D7DE52EC3BD1420" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as abscissa of vein 2m-cu above bulla, respectively.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DE3274EDABFA8E4B317E35867886422A" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677626" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" start="Figure 8" startId="F8">
